Hellenic Telecommunications
Organization SA (HTO)  is considering the introduction of a four-day
working week for employees as a way to cut operating costs,
 Kathimerini  reported.  The move would reduce annual wage costs for the company,
known as OTE, by as much as 20 percent, or about 100 million
euros ($145 million), the newspaper reported, without saying how
it obtained the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
